      </div>
      <h2>What is AMH?</h2>
      <p>Anti-Müllerian Hormone (AMH) is produced by the small follicles in your ovaries and directly reflects your ovarian reserve — the number of eggs you have remaining. Unlike other hormones, AMH stays stable throughout your menstrual cycle, so it can be measured on any day of the month with a simple blood test.</p>
      <p style="margin-top:10px;">AMH is measured in ng/mL. Most labs in India report results within 24–48 hours, and no doctor's prescription is required at walk-in diagnostic centres.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="fc-gate-info-card">
      <div class="fc-gate-info-card__icon fc-info-icon--amber">
